text.__SUMMARY__: Mumiola gradatula is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Caribbean Sea
Costa Rica
Gulf of Mexico
Hispaniola
Jamaica
Lesser Antilles
Panama
